  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Given `npm run build` in each solution, when complete, then a single-file HTML web resource is produced.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given each Custom Page mounted in Vite dev with mock URL params, when rendered, then DataGrid renders with Matter context filter applied.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given each Custom Page's main.tsx, when grepped, then `applyStylesToPortals={true}` is on the root FluentProvider.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given line count, when measured (excluding boilerplate), then each main.tsx is ≤60 lines.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <ui-tests>
    <test name="Custom Page loads in dialog mode">
      <url>https://{org}.crm.dynamics.com/main.aspx?pagetype=webresource&amp;webresourceName=sprk_kpiassessmentspage.html&amp;data=matterId%3D{guid}</url>
      <steps>
        <step>Open Custom Page in dialog mode</step>
        <step>Verify DataGrid renders with KPI rows filtered to current Matter</step>
        <step>Click a row → verify navigateToForm opens</step>
        <step>Toggle dark mode → verify portals adapt (NFR-11)</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>Renders correctly, filter applied, dark mode portal-clean</expected>
    </test>
  </ui-tests>

  <notes>
    Both Custom Pages share a shell pattern — only differences are configId + Invoice's Mark Paid handler registration (if UQ-05 is R1). Keep them lean per FR-CON-03/04 "~50 lines". Resist adding logic here — anything beyond URL parse + mount belongs in the framework, not the shell.
  </notes>

